12/12/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski and Chief of General Staff Metodi Stamboliski welcomed the country's 29-member peacekeeping contingent home from Iraq on Wednesday (10 December) and awarded them military medals. 
The troops spent six months in Iraq.
Also Wednesday, US Deputy Defence Secretary Paul Wolfowitz announced that Macedonia is included in the list of 63 countries allowed to bid for lucrative Iraq reconstruction contracts. 
(Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 11/12/03)
